DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Alkaline Phosphatase Eligibility Determination Ind-2
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the yes/no indicator related to a laboratory procedure for alkaline phosphatase and patient/participant eligibility.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Alkaline Phosphatase Eligibility Determination
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information relating to the laboratory procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for alkaline phosphatase, an enzyme that catalyzes the conversion of an orthophosphoric monoester and water to an alcohol and orthophosphate, as a method of determining if a subject is suitable for enrollment in a study according specific protocol criteria and procedures.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: An enzyme that catalyzes the conversion of an orthophosphoric monoester and water to an alcohol and orthophosphate. EC 3.1.3.1.:Criteria to determine eligibility of patients for medical care programs and services.

Concepts.definition: An enzyme that catalyses the cleavage of inorganic phosphate non-specifically from a wide variety of phosphate esters and having a high (greater than 8) pH optimum.
The act of determining if a subject is suitable for enrollment in a study according specific protocol criteria and procedures.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: trial-specific criteria that a patient must meet to be enrolled.
